TY  - JOUR
T1  - Is Group Productivity Loss the Rule or The Exception? Effects of Culture and Group-Based Motivation
AU  - Erez, Miriam
AU  - Somech, Anit
Y1  - 1996/12/01
PY  - 1996
DA  - 1996/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/257067
DO  - 10.5465/257067
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 1513
EP  - 1537
VL  - 39
IS  - 6
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study examined four causes of group performance loss: goal specificity, communication, incentives for goal attainment, and high versus low cultural collectivism. Subjects were managers from Israeli kibbutzim (63 individuals) and cities (59 individuals) who worked on a simulated task requiring them to evaluate résumés. We used a two-by-three-by-four design in which sample, goal, and test condition were varied to test hypotheses. Group performance loss occurred only for urban respondents with a do-your-best goal and team task.
AB  - This study examined four causes of group performance loss: goal specificity, communication, incentives for goal attainment, and high versus low cultural collectivism. Subjects were managers from Israeli kibbutzim (63 individuals) and cities (59 individuals) who worked on a simulated task requiring them to evaluate résumés. We used a two-by-three-by-four design in which sample, goal, and test condition were varied to test hypotheses. Group performance loss occurred only for urban respondents with a do-your-best goal and team task.
